{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "5444b75c66aa7c74", "candidate": {"id": "cand-030", "name": "Fatou Diallo", "raw_cv": "FATOU DIALLO\nfatou.diallo@email.com | Remote (Paris, France) \u2014 open to London relocation\n\nINFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEER / DEVOPS\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nInfrastructure engineer with 7 years of experience managing hybrid cloud and on-premises environments. Expert in multi-cloud infrastructure (AWS + GCP), Terraform, and Linux systems. Strong background in telecommunications and media streaming infrastructure.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Infrastructure Engineer \u2014 Canal+ Group, Paris (2020\u2013present)\n- Own hybrid cloud infrastructure for Canal+'s streaming platform serving 8M+ subscribers\n- Led lift-and-shift of video transcoding workloads from on-prem GPU servers to AWS EC2 (G4 instances), reducing capacity costs 45%\n- Designed multi-region failover architecture using AWS Route53, ALB, and cross-region replication\n- Managed a team of 3 infrastructure engineers; introduced IaC discipline with Terraform\n\nInfrastructure Engineer \u2014 Orange Business Services, Paris (2017\u20132020)\n- Managed network and compute infrastructure for enterprise telecom clients\n- Introduced Ansible for configuration management across 200+ bare-metal servers\n- Built monitoring stack (Prometheus + Grafana) replacing legacy Nagios setup\n\nSKILLS\nAWS (EC2, ECS, RDS, S3, Route53, CloudFront, IAM), GCP (GCE, GCS, Cloud Run), Terraform, Ansible, Linux (RHEL, Ubuntu), Docker, Kubernetes (basic), Python, Bash, Prometheus, Grafana, Nginx\n\nEDUCATION\nEngineering Degree (Dipl\u00f4me d'Ing\u00e9nieur) \u2014 T\u00e9l\u00e9com Paris (2013\u20132016)\n\nLANGUAGES\nFrench (native), English (fluent), Wolof (native)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nFrench citizen \u2014 requires UK visa sponsorship", "raw_linkedin": "Infrastructure engineer with seven years running hybrid cloud environments, currently at Canal+ managing streaming infrastructure for 8 million subscribers. My background in telecoms means I'm comfortable at every layer of the stack \u2014 from bare metal to cloud-native. I'm particularly interested in the cost and reliability trade-offs of hybrid architectures. French national, based in Paris but seriously considering a move to London for the right role. Would require visa sponsorship. Open to senior infrastructure or platform engineering positions.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Fatou, thanks for joining remotely. Tell me about the transcoding migration.\n\nFatou: Canal+ had a large on-premises GPU cluster for video transcoding \u2014 H.264, H.265, some AV1. The hardware was ageing and the capex refresh was going to be significant. I built the business case for moving to AWS G4 instances, which give us access to NVIDIA T4 GPUs on demand. The key insight was that our transcoding workload is bursty \u2014 live sports events create huge spikes \u2014 and on-prem you have to provision for peak. With AWS we can scale to 10x capacity for a six-hour window during a Champions League final and then scale back down. We saved 45% on capacity costs in year one.\n\nInterviewer: How do you approach Terraform at scale?\n\nFatou: We use a modular approach \u2014 reusable modules for common patterns like a standard VPC setup, an ECS service definition, an RDS instance with sensible defaults. Teams can compose these rather than writing from scratch. We also use Terragrunt to manage the module versions across environments, which keeps things DRY. State is in S3 with DynamoDB locking.\n\nInterviewer: You'd need a UK visa. Have you looked into the process?\n\nFatou: Yes, I've researched the Skilled Worker route. My role should qualify and I'd expect the process to take 6\u20138 weeks. It's not a barrier as long as the employer is a licensed sponsor.\n\nInterviewer: Salary expectations?\n\nFatou: I'm at \u20ac95,000. For London I'd be looking at \u00a390\u2013100,000 depending on the package.", "years_experience": 7.0, "skills": ["AWS", "EC2", "ECS", "RDS", "S3", "Route53", "CloudFront", "IAM", "GCP", "GCE", "GCS", "Cloud Run", "Terraform", "Terragrunt", "Ansible", "Linux", "RHEL", "Ubuntu", "Docker", "Kubernetes", "Python", "Bash", "Prometheus", "Grafana", "Nginx"], "industries": ["telecommunications", "media", "streaming", "cloud infrastructure"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.8, "constraints": [{"id": "baabc38c", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "French citizen; requires UK visa sponsorship for relocation", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "fe5c4558", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u20ac95,000", "canonical_key": "salary_current", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "EUR"}, {"id": "64e1397b", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "London salary expectation \u00a390\u2013100,000 depending on package", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "dc548cc0", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "London salary expectation upper range \u00a390\u2013100,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 100000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "9079f5c0", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Open to London relocation from Paris", "canonical_key": "location_london", "value": "London", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "64648203", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Currently based in Paris; remote working implied as acceptable", "canonical_key": "remote_capable", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.75, "currency": null}, {"id": "0d77f1df", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Open to senior infrastructure or platform engineering positions", "canonical_key": "role_type", "value": "senior infrastructure or platform engineering", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "66164130", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "technical_interest", "description": "Interested in cost and reliability trade-offs of hybrid architectures", "canonical_key": null, "value": "hybrid architecture optimization", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.8, "currency": null}], "discipline": "other"}, "embedding": [0.00775146484375, -0.01140594482421875, 0.06597900390625, -0.0167388916015625, 0.0015239715576171875, 0.00853729248046875, -0.01010894775390625, 0.043182373046875, -0.019378662109375, 0.00536346435546875, 0.0309295654296875, -0.06060791015625, -0.017547607421875, -0.03485107421875, 0.0204315185546875, 0.07452392578125, -0.03509521484375, 0.004940032958984375, -0.0137481689453125, 0.02899169921875, 0.002704620361328125, 0.01468658447265625, -0.0205078125, 0.0306854248046875, 0.01467132568359375, -0.0027141571044921875, -0.0304718017578125, 0.030517578125, -0.0340576171875, -0.0379638671875, 0.05389404296875, -0.031341552734375, -0.0533447265625, 0.0435791015625, 0.052886962890625, -0.012115478515625, 0.0036640167236328125, 0.05609130859375, 0.0304107666015625, 0.01131439208984375, -0.027862548828125, 0.0016565322875976562, 0.0194244384765625, -0.01102447509765625, -0.0029926300048828125, 0.00420379638671875, -0.00311279296875, 0.005634307861328125, 0.0118865966796875, 0.023040771484375, 0.023101806640625, -0.0220489501953125, 0.0014514923095703125, 0.039581298828125, 0.026214599609375, 0.00265121459